				<title>(no title)</title>
				<link>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-609883/sympathy-for-an-empath#post-2320017</link>
				<description></description>
				<pubDate>Fri, 19 Jun 2015 00:58:07 +0000</pubDate>
				<wikidot:authorName>Mr Gehz</wikidot:authorName>				<wikidot:authorUserId>2173208</wikidot:authorUserId>				<content:encoded>
					<![CDATA[
						 <p>I see your point, but the fun about these stories is that you can read one and click a link or search for another one to understand the one you are reading and this may lead you to an SCP fiile you didn't know you might find interesting. (Note: this experience is greatly magnified if you are new to the site.) The thing about Redd is ok in my opinion but I know that this needs something more dramatic, powerful, swift, to make it better.</p> 
				 	]]>
				</content:encoded>							</item>
					<item>
				<guid>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-609883#post-2045253</guid>
				<title>(no title)</title>
				<link>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-609883/sympathy-for-an-empath#post-2045253</link>
				<description></description>
				<pubDate>Wed, 04 Jun 2014 04:25:56 +0000</pubDate>
				<wikidot:authorName>thedeadlymoose</wikidot:authorName>				<wikidot:authorUserId>732274</wikidot:authorUserId>				<content:encoded>
					<![CDATA[
						 <p><sub>may or may not have had the same reaction</sub></p> <p>I really want to like this, but there's just not enough here to make the snippet worthwhile. :( No vote.</p> <p>I would honestly recommend &#8212; not <em>expanding</em> it, but <em>changing</em> some of the detail to make it more interesting.</p> <p>Just to take one example: &quot;I never thought they would treat me like Redd…&quot; &#8212; bleh, this is obvious, and not interesting. Why not a reference to something we totally don't understand at all?</p> 
				 	]]>
				</content:encoded>							</item>
